Flyers Beat Sabres 5-2 to Win NHL Playoff Series; Canadiens Force Game 7

-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 
2011-04-27T02:18:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-27/flyers-beat-sabres-5-2-to-win-nhl-playoff-series-canadiens-force-game-7.html
The  Philadelphia Flyers  beat the
Buffalo Sabres 5-2 to win their National Hockey League first-
round playoff series, while the Montreal Canadiens beat the
Boston Bruins 2-1 to force a deciding game.  Braydon Coburn,  Danny Briere , James van Riemsdyk, Ville
Leino and Daniel Carcillo scored for the Flyers at Wells Fargo
Center in Philadelphia in Game 7 of the Eastern Conference
series.  Also tonight, the Stanley Cup champion Chicago Blackhawks
visit the Vancouver Canucks looking to become the fourth team in
NHL history to rally from a 3-0 deficit to win a seven-game
playoff series. The Canucks finished the regular season with the
best record in the league.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dex McLuskey at 
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net  